---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Catalyst Neuromorphic" description="How Catalyst Neuromorphic handles your data">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2" style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-white/30 text-sm mb-12">Last updated: 25 February 2026</p>

    <div class="prose-legal">
      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>Catalyst Neuromorphic ("we", "us") is a business registered in the United Kingdom. We operate the Catalyst Cloud platform at catalyst-neuromorphic.com and api.catalyst-neuromorphic.com.</p>
      <p>Data controller contact: <a href="mailto:henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com">henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com</a></p>

      <h2>2. What data we collect</h2>
      <p>When you use our Service, we collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> email address, hashed password, display name</li>
        <li><strong>OAuth data:</strong> GitHub or Google user ID and email (if you sign up via OAuth)</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information:</strong> processed and stored by Stripe. We store your Stripe customer ID but never your card details.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> job submissions, compute time, API key usage, timestamps</li>
        <li><strong>Technical data:</strong> IP address, browser user-agent string, session tokens</li>
        <li><strong>Network definitions:</strong> the spiking neural network configurations you submit for simulation</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use your data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>To provide the Service:</strong> run your simulations, manage your account, process payments (legal basis: contract)</li>
        <li><strong>To communicate with you:</strong> send verification codes, password resets, payment receipts, and service updates (legal basis: contract)</li>
        <li><strong>To improve the Service:</strong> aggregate, anonymised usage statistics to understand platform performance (legal basis: legitimate interest)</li>
        <li><strong>To prevent abuse:</strong> rate limiting by IP address, fraud detection (legal basis: legitimate interest)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell your data. We do <strong>not</strong> use your network definitions or simulation results for any purpose other than providing the Service to you.</p>

      <h2>4. Third-party processors</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services to operate the platform:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> (stripe.com) — payment processing. Stripe's privacy policy applies to payment data.</li>
        <li><strong>Fly.io</strong> (fly.io) — API hosting. Servers located in London, UK.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> (cloudflare.com) — website hosting, CDN, DNS, and DDoS protection.</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> (resend.com) — transactional email delivery (verification codes, receipts).</li>
        <li><strong>GitHub / Google</strong> — OAuth authentication (only if you choose to sign in via these providers).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data:</strong> retained while your account is active. Deleted within 30 days of account deletion.</li>
        <li><strong>Job results:</strong> retained for 90 days after completion, then automatically purged.</li>
        <li><strong>Payment records:</strong> retained for 7 years as required by UK tax law.</li>
        <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> IP addresses and request metadata retained for 30 days.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Your rights (UK GDPR)</h2>
      <p>Under UK data protection law, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> request a copy of all data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> correct inaccurate data via your account settings</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> delete your account and all associated data</li>
        <li><strong>Portability:</strong> export your data in machine-readable JSON format</li>
        <li><strong>Objection:</strong> object to processing based on legitimate interest</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> request we limit how we process your data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise these rights, use the Account page in the console or email us at <a href="mailto:henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com">henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com</a>. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

      <h2>7. Data export and deletion</h2>
      <p>You can export all your data as a JSON file from the Account page in the console. You can delete your account at any time, which will permanently remove all your data including networks, jobs, API keys, usage history, and billing records (except where retention is required by law).</p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>We protect your data with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Passwords hashed with bcrypt</li>
        <li>API keys stored as SHA-256 hashes (never in plaintext)</li>
        <li>Session tokens hashed before storage</li>
        <li>HTTPS encryption for all connections</li>
        <li>WAL-mode SQLite with foreign key constraints for data integrity</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Cookies</h2>
      <p>We use localStorage (not cookies) to store your session token. We do not use tracking cookies, analytics cookies, or advertising cookies. Cloudflare may set a security cookie (__cf_bm) for bot detection.</p>

      <h2>10. International transfers</h2>
      <p>Your data is primarily stored and processed in the UK (London). Stripe may process payment data in the EU/US under their own data processing agreements. Cloudflare's CDN may cache static content globally but does not cache personal data.</p>

      <h2>11. Children</h2>
      <p>The Service is not directed at individuals under 16. We do not knowingly collect data from children. If you believe a child has created an account, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

      <h2>12. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email. The "Last updated" date at the top indicates the most recent revision.</p>

      <h2>13. Contact and complaints</h2>
      <p>Contact our data controller: <a href="mailto:henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com">henry@catalyst-neuromorphic.com</a></p>
      <p>If you are not satisfied with our response, you can complain to the UK Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-legal h2 {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .prose-legal p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .prose-legal ul {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    font-size: 0.925rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose-legal li {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    list-style-type: disc;
  }
  .prose-legal a {
    color: #3B82F6;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .prose-legal a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .prose-legal strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }
</style>
